  "text": "The genes encoding for S100A3 and S100A8 were also upregulated. These proteins belong to a family of low-molecularweight Ca 2ϩ -binding proteins of the EF-hand type known as S100. Previous work has implicated S100 proteins in Ca 2ϩ -dependent regulation of intracellular and extracellular functions such as protein phosphorylation, calcium homeostasis, inflammation, and regulation of the dynamics of cytoskeleton components [CITATION_1] .",
